line_1: On Sands, as dead, the Cramp-Fish lies supine,
line_2: Conscious of secret Pow'r, a Gift divine,

line_1: So when the mind imbrutes in sloth supine,
line_2: Sharp pangs awake her energy divine.

line_1: See how astonished now the crowd supine,
line_2: In tottering masses o'er their heads decline

line_1: To rouse the vain, the giddy, and supine,
line_2: Stalk o'er the gloomy grave, Muse! be it thine

line_1: Take, if ye can, ye careless and supine!
line_2: Counsel and caution from a voice like mine;

line_1: Let me not sink in sloth supine,
line_2: While all creation at thy shrine

line_1: Than yawn out the dull droning life supine
line_2: Better to die with glory, than recline

line_1: I greedy gaze, you sleep supine,
